  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering the Scope**\n\nI\'m currently assessing the scale of this project. It seems we\'re dealing with a substantial web application, perhaps a full-stack design given the geo-spatial data. It will need to incorporate detailed information from 60 underground sites in Naples, a formidable challenge.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Monolith**\n\nI\'ve moved past initial scope assessment and am now analyzing the provided monolithic HTML. It appears the user already supplied a comprehensive structure encompassing all 60 sites, Trips, styles, and data. My focus is now on transforming this monolith into a modular React/Vite application as requested, so I can start by separating the concerns.\n\n\n**Assessing Available Tools**\n\nI\'ve evaluated the available skills, and it looks like I need to focus on a few key areas. I\'ll be concentrating on `focus-mode` to ensure a smooth workflow. I\'ll need to leverage `gemini-api` and `gemini-interactions-api` for any necessary natural language processing and integration, and I have good support for `google-maps-platform` for mapping functionality. While I have the ability for image generation and integrations, those won\'t be crucial in this implementation, and I will be using `Deck.gl` and `MapLibre` to make it \'fly to the point\' as requested.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am ready to process the Napoli Sotterranea Beta 1 - Sistema Geospaziale Unicum project! I will read the project files to understand our structural boundaries, then build a modular, high-fidelity application in React + TypeScript with a dark, historical material aesthetic (Gold, Ink, Parchment, Stone).\n\nLet\'s check our package dependencies."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 868282037
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
