    thinking: "**Revising App.tsx Code**\n\nI\'m currently focused on incorporating the sidebar layout and header elements, per the \"Sophisticated Dark\" design pattern. I\'m prioritizing the structure, which includes the project label in uppercase and the majestic title, making sure both are styled as described. Next, I\'ll be working on integrating the design specs for other elements like the subtitle and menu.\n\n\n**Adjusting Main Layout**\n\nNow, I\'m integrating the design for the main map area, focusing on making the map responsive by setting the `h-0` class for height-zero. I\'m moving the detailed panel footer to the bottom of the map wrapper, assigning it a fixed height of `245px`. This should improve layout clarity. I\'m also addressing the design of the inner search/filter area and the scrollable sites list. I am working on the copywrite/credits at the bottom of the sidebar.\n\n\n**Refining Detail Panel**\n\nI\'m now implementing the design details for the site detail panel, giving it a height of `245px` and matching the specified color palette. I\'m focusing on handling both selected and unselected site states, using the same layout but with a different message. Currently, I\'m working on the two-column structure: the left column containing header and content. I\'m implementing the conditional content rendering based on the site selection state.\n\n\n**Defining Site Detail Content**\n\nI am now focusing on refining the content within the site detail panel, especially the text displayed based on the `selectedSite.category`. I\'m working on conditional rendering to correctly display \'Acquedotto\', \'Necropoli\', \'Rifugio\', or \'Ipogeo\' based on the site category. Also, I\'m working on integrating the site-specific metrics, including depth and humidity, into the panel. I\'m taking care to display \'\342\200\223\342\200\223\' where necessary. I am now working on the metric\'s data formatting.\n\n\n"
