    modified_response: "I have successfully integrated the **Sophisticated Dark** design theme into the **Napoli Sotterranea Beta 1 - Sistema Geospaziale Unicum** application:\n\n### Design & Aesthetic Advancements\n- **Luxury Contrast Balance**: Re-architectured the layout from a dark-on-dark look into a high-contrast format. The left sidebar remains set in an intense ink-black tone (`#0A0806`) adorned with golden boundaries (`#C9A84C`), while the detailed bottom panel shifts to an eye-catching historical parchment background (`#F5EDD8`).\n- **Playfair Display Display Headings**: Styled the monumental titles and interactive site cards with elegant serif display lettering, creating a physical, antique book layout.\n- **Illustrated Vector Icon Glyphs**: Replaced default badges with dynamic vector icons that render the structural architectural hallmarks for Acquedotti, Necropoli, Rifugi, and Ipogei with perfect precision.\n- **Dynamic Dossier Ledger**: Shifted the historical details panel to the bottom of the map view area, allowing the descriptions and metadata gauges to enjoy generous horizontal margins.\n\n### Integrated Interactions\n- **Map & Directory FlyTo Sync**: Selecting card elements inside the sidebar or clicking interactive marker hotspots on the map initiates a smooth camera flight to the site coordinates, rotating the perspective to a $60^\\circ$ pitch.\n- **Aqueduct Water Flow Simulation**: Animates real-time, historical water routing trajectories beneath the modern street network under active Deck.gl rendering loops."
