rsion mismatch. The `package.json` specifies `maplibre-gl@^5.24.0`, but the HTML loads `maplibre-gl@3.x` via unpkg. `deck.gl@latest` (v9.x) likely expects a newer MapLibre GL version, causing the \"Script error.\" I\'m now certain this is a major source of the bug. I also need to evaluate the safety of direct imports. I\'m going to look at the differences in versions.\n\n\n**Verifying Module Imports**\n\nI\'m now running a test build with direct imports to see if this resolves the runtime error. I also need to understand why this runtime error is happening. The error is a \"Script error\" which points to cross-origin issues with scripts. I\'m going to look through `node_modules` to explore the potential for using standard import statements, completely removing the reliance on unpkg.com scripts, which are often blocked by corporate proxies or fail due to CORS. I\'ll also see if `\"deck.gl\"` and `\"maplibre-gl\"` can actually be imported. I\'m going to check `UndergroundMap.tsx` next!\n\n\n"
