  search_web {
    query: "deck.gl core class Deck constructor options container or parent"
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHOL1w5kj2thQxCuykcRMcHSrlwlqjFrScF3133HkUOX_V7cGmC4TT0J0Izp5q_-CJsbJSiEeC9iexNpTZPccYX9sVe375nhC3uNLVqzwjvbP9Z8mk_KLEFKJyCX4HTJDCoXxHZCY8M"
      title: "deck.gl"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHysGUs0S5JTeXtRXOoxA2Tt1ZsKEBRNgRoLFPn5fSBz-XHCG68s6JAEHzs-mv7zjtyKYDiifHAnsNwBHZzc0wi4p7Nx0TH8zHVWsY_HXxXaU1FwxU8wObgj7Jj0arzhyXi9kl3LK0whymGJoA="
      title: "github.com"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGQuYtbzL-s74m2VARw-l3XC1sofTovMDO2jfryL5Ofy5jv5O20i_xndjmzLb6jZbtNW1t_SBlnPgKTtfxz19bCpcYu8QuPZZ6ZYvgvVjk19Znk1NuJtCGjGFFYsNy2o9xARnCkNB_5R_g="
      title: "deck.gl"
    }
    summary: "In deck.gl, both `parent` and `container` are options used to specify where the deck.gl canvas should be appended in the DOM, though they are associated with different classes and have slightly different contexts:\n\n*   **`parent`**: This option is used in the core `Deck` class constructor. It specifies the HTML element to which the automatically created `canvas` element for rendering will be appended. If not provided, it defaults to `document.body`[1]. The `parent` option is supported across all flavors of `Deck`.[2]\n*   **`container`**: This option is found in the `DeckGL` scripting interface, which extends the core `Deck` class with additional features, such as Mapbox integration[3]. The `container` can be either an `HTMLDivElement` or its ID (a string)[3]. deck.gl will append its canvas within this specified container, and the canvas will be resized to fill the container[3]. Similar to `parent`, the default for `container` is `document.body`[3]. The `container` option in `DeckGL` also implicitly handles some base map integration if Mapbox GL JS is included[2].\n\nIn essence, if you are directly using the `Deck` class, you would use the `parent` option. If you are using the `DeckGL` scripting interface (often for simpler setups or when integrating with mapping libraries), you would use the `container` option[3][2].\n\nSources:\n[1] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHOL1w5kj2thQxCuykcRMcHSrlwlqjFrScF3133HkUOX_V7cGmC4TT0J0Izp5q_-CJsbJSiEeC9iexNpTZPccYX9sVe375nhC3uNLVqzwjvbP9Z8mk_KLEFKJyCX4HTJDCoXxHZCY8M)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHysGUs0S5JTeXtRXOoxA2Tt1ZsKEBRNgRoLFPn5fSBz-XHCG68s6JAEHzs-mv7zjtyKYDiifHAnsNwBHZzc0wi4p7Nx0TH8zHVWsY_HXxXaU1FwxU8wObgj7Jj0arzhyXi9kl3LK0whymGJoA=)\n[3] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGQuYtbzL-s74m2VARw-l3XC1sofTovMDO2jfryL5Ofy5jv5O20i_xndjmzLb6jZbtNW1t_SBlnPgKTtfxz19bCpcYu8QuPZZ6ZYvgvVjk19Znk1NuJtCGjGFFYsNy2o9xARnCkNB_5R_g=)"
    search_type: SEARCH_WEB_TYPE_WEB
  }
}
