    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGNoumh0suGs6Awk38sOmwVYyxqooV6soANkiWtl824jpJYtY7WL8w-0VGZyC1vnbvf2ZGEpdmUbn6bRPL490cuCJFUFWo9ezoJEcv3GttDAx6S9bC0EDrjdw=="
      title: "deck.gl"
    }
    summary: "In `deck.gl`, the terms \"parent\" and \"container\" refer to the HTML element where the `deck.gl` canvas is rendered. The specific prop used depends on whether you are using the core `Deck` class, the `DeckGL` React component, or `MapboxOverlay`.\n\nFor the core `Deck` class, part of `@deck.gl/core`, the `parent` property is available within its constructor\'s `DeckProps`. This `parent` property expects an `HTMLElement` and defaults to `document.body`. It specifies the container to which the auto-created canvas for the `Deck` instance will be appended[1][2].\n\nWhen utilizing the `DeckGL` React component, you should use the `container` prop. This `container` can be either a `DOMElement` or a `String` representing the element\'s ID, and it also defaults to `document.body`. The `deck.gl` canvas is then appended to and automatically resized to fill this specified container[3].\n\nIn the context of `MapboxOverlay`, the `parent` and `canvas` props are not directly exposed as context creation is managed internally. Instead, the `MapboxOverlay` constructor accepts a `container` option, which is the ID of the HTML element where the Mapbox map (and consequently the `deck.gl` layers) will be rendered[4][5].\n\nIt\'s also worth noting that `DeckProps` defines the set of properties that can be passed to the `Deck` class constructor[1][6]. However, when using specialized components like `MapboxOverlay`, some `DeckProps` such as `parent`, `canvas`, `viewState`, `initialViewState`, and `controller` are either omitted or managed internally by the overlay[6][4]. Additionally, `deck.gl` v9.3 introduced a `_container` prop for widgets, allowing them to be rendered into any parent container[7].\n\nSources:\n[1] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEVSFAOwyRdF2fb4vcaqvFr6aYhfRRKL3Hj3s964U7ZPjDZywDV-n9R3HJMC_y8rDVCaWQXJ5c0fZ2Ps0zzvuRHYurhZ2Is5jVspR6z6l4FrlX8ITb7osYU8ExJ7EIwFtodDjHi5r33)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGxbmvs8kQxn2nQVzVQUfmnP0hC5gWmsHHHbIUJsij5aDn8gv2-gubOj-cjEt8C-EDFM1dVapyvGPhewyCz7bCkMRLmR6f6pC2a7HVrWoHR11LL6cmGYtut65KekcbbyXI8wc0Ok_YhrEtCa7E=)\n[3] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFvjLfm8L0D2l-p_VUVsTH4yzsj2EzLfPOpdwnbemsjj0t4grEK0wvOPF_nhlC7kpFO7HsRyqB-GN-Am--dvC0Q9y9Y5edS_ifco08BfySQY0Hg5A8jFZBT2aDRFcZN40GrhrWyHGlohGI=)\n[4] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEjlLZUdet8eAFKT9d0Yolz0_a6SWIX-IqW-lt0fEhIzYFgHBqxoC_r_vcsdgJSBTnwM2n3_97lwcNOkLQkQfm6S9qFsR7Q6ve_stqLRsBiX53K9853aEKIbLyvCsp5vsAL6bPn6j9l4T93cthugD7-A1IqtRNEfXUEMc3UtSbxQox_Mu7kS19UhCh3qA812Wj07m0=)\n[5] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGbzD-jgApN6UzJuuxjnBjfE_MGUb9e4GEUUk2eoYAf_kHD-j5zk7PoGQ_-WymC6W-wMSe3kbGn5OCcTR05S1QooS7hHt_XYhqLksYMj6YhBLYETjjfagr6lqQGNSvlkVo8NGLchYCTL7H3xVDn_tcgZ6uU)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDJldpPNniXrxynUh8w7cu-Q-9U3V3b2biX6MEL_EmyRYehhgkE-RXU7bMrhrwakTIEF6C7L19W9-TDxrKQRvyGlrAAYIyReVsw73Z52sQMsvn9o8DfrJUj3LQfjKt1JmpVi4784pXULtmENWnYlfaML4R91pYb2lT7btb0nFhPjjlwLexTMMhqk7JIQ==)\n[7] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGNoumh0suGs6Awk38sOmwVYyxqooV6soANkiWtl824jpJYtY7WL8w-0VGZyC1vnbvf2ZGEpdmUbn6bRPL490cuCJFUFWo9ezoJEcv3GttDAx6S9bC0EDrjdw==)"
