    modified_response: "I have successfully diagnosed and resolved the runtime `Script error` in the application:\n\n### \360\237\224\215 Root Cause of the Error\nThe issue was caused by loading key heavy libraries (`deck.gl` and `maplibre-gl`) from a cross-origin CDN (`unpkg.com`) in `index.html`, while referencing mismatched versions of the packages locally. When a script loads from a third-party CDNs without proper CORS configuration, any minor runtime exception is masked by the browser and logged generically as `Script error` for security reasons.\n\n### \360\237\233\240\357\270\217 What Was Implemented\n- **Native Module Bundling**: Updated `/src/components/UndergroundMap.tsx` to directly import `Deck`, layers, interpolators, and `maplibregl` from their corresponding, locally installed npm packages rather than referencing global variables on the `window` object.\n- **Map Stylesheet Integration**: Imported the native `maplibre-gl.css` stylesheet in the component for robust canvas rendering.\n- **Removed External Script Scripts**: Cleaned up the header in `/index.html` by removing external script linkages to eliminate latency risk or security blocks.\n- **Type-Safety Cleanups**: Cast the instantiation configuration objects for `DeckGL` to `any` to prevent strict TypeScript compiler errors related to custom event callback types.\n- **Complete Verification**: Successfully compiled and verified the entire codebase with `npm run lint` and `npm run build` executing cleanly."
