  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Investigating Deck.gl Integration**\n\nI\'m currently focused on how Deck.gl interacts with MapLibre, particularly when initiated programmatically with `new Deck(...)`. I\'m exploring the integration between MapLibre and Deck.gl, and more specifically, how the `mapStyle` setting behaves when used without loading Mapbox resources.\n\n\n**Clarifying Deck.gl Instantiation**\n\nI\'ve realized that directly instantiating `Deck` doesn\'t inherently integrate with MapLibre or manage its styles without specific configuration or a separate map instance. My focus is now on the conventional methods for merging Deck.gl with MapLibre: either using `MapboxOverlay` as a control or configuring Deck.gl to manage the MapLibre map underneath. Additionally, I\'m trying to work out how the original codebase had `const { DeckGL } = (window as any).deck;`. It seems like using the unpkg CDN is important, which will expose the deck object.\n\n\n**Analyzing Deck.gl Imports**\n\nI\'m now investigating the imports and how `deck.gl` handles map rendering. I\'m focusing on whether `Deck` itself handles the map rendering or needs specific imports, like using the `maplibregl` parameter or appropriate module loading. I\'m also checking browser console errors for clues, and looking up methods for MapLibre integration in Deck.gl\'s documentation, and I\'m focusing on how `Deck` handles options like `mapStyle` and `maplibregl` in v9, to see if `@deck.gl/react` is necessary.\n\n\n**Pinpointing Module Imports**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the proper import path for the `Deck` class. It turns out that `Deck` is exported from `@deck.gl/core`. I\'m also confirming that instantiating `new Deck()` doesn\'t inherently create a basemap, and in fact, in v9, Deck.gl will render to its own canvas unless it is specifically given a map instance. That means it is the same as v8. Finally, I\'m now looking into how the original code worked, and I am reviewing the `<script>` import statements.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will search the web for documentation on how to properly integrate MapLibre and Deck.gl in a standalone ESM environment."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 767904395
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
