      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGzdw3WumP5wscSaMdFv5kiMkqZVyWy4DD2YWZDfQvnTrtwSX8UbkQAi9Q5qmu-TVXBY4SUkZoonA4ur4FjuUZOShGZ0I0qix7HsoNjotBWthjC9rfupvks0fydPxm3pPNu_ioITLpjYNh-F47Qu-ZtK-oBWuYeZqILokBTUnvnbJs="
      title: "maplibre.org"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHxxmIXV7puvEzJ1LFivo9REPJW6wsmQfsalrp2F_Kx_Cj4GwzMrYTsLEiJw1t-HoTcpmHrMoUxtnomCH9oHoHT6vtz3w8esaflCHk="
      title: "deck.gl"
    }
    summary: "`deck.gl` can be seamlessly integrated with `MapLibre GL JS` in various modes, with `MapboxOverlay` being a recommended approach for managing this integration, including in standalone JavaScript applications. `MapboxOverlay` acts as a control for `MapLibre GL JS` to synchronize `deck.gl` layers with the base map.[1][2][3][4]\n\nThere are three primary integration modes when combining `deck.gl` with `MapLibre GL JS`:[1]\n\n1.  **Interleaved Mode**: In this mode, `deck.gl` layers are rendered directly into the WebGL2 context created by `MapLibre`. This allows for a mix of `deck.gl` and `MapLibre` layers, enabling features like `deck.gl` surfaces appearing beneath map labels or correct 3D occlusion between objects. To achieve this, you use `MapboxOverlay` with the `interleaved: true` option. This mode requires `maplibre-gl` version 3 or later.[1][2][3]\n2.  **Overlaid Mode**: This renders `deck.gl` in a separate canvas positioned within `MapLibre`\'s controls container. It\'s suitable when direct interleaving of layers isn\'t a requirement, but you still want to leverage `MapLibre GL JS` features such as controls (e.g., `NavigationControl`, `Popup`) or plugins. This is supported by `MapboxOverlay` with `interleaved: false`.[1]\n3.  **Reverse-Controlled Mode**: In this setup, `deck.gl` renders above the `MapLibre` container and takes over interaction handling. This mode is useful when you need to implement custom pointer input handling, manage multiple maps, or use a map that doesn\'t fill the entire canvas (with `deck.gl`\'s multi-view feature). `MapLibre GL JS` controls and plugins are not compatible in this mode; instead, components from `@deck.gl/widgets` should be used.[1]\n\n**Using `MapboxOverlay` with `MapLibre GL JS`**\n\nThe `@deck.gl/mapbox` module provides `MapboxOverlay`, which is an implementation of Mapbox GL JS\'s `IControl` API and works equivalently with `MapLibre GL JS`.[2][3] It synchronizes a `deck.gl MapView` with the `maplibre-gl` camera, ensuring geospatial alignment between the base map and `deck.gl` layers.[2]\n\nTo use `MapboxOverlay` in a standalone JavaScript environment with `MapLibre GL JS`:\n*   Include the standalone bundles for both `maplibre-gl` and `deck.gl` in your HTML.[5][2]\n*   Initialize your `maplibregl.Map` instance with your desired map style and initial view state.[5]\n*   Create a new `MapboxOverlay` instance, passing your `deck.gl` layers to its `layers` option. You can also specify `interleaved: true` or `interleaved: false` based on your rendering needs.[1]\n*   Add the `MapboxOverlay` instance to your `maplibregl.Map` using `map.addControl(overlay)`.[6][7]\n\n**`MapboxOverlay` Options and `maplibregl` Interaction:**\n\nThe `MapboxOverlay` constructor accepts options similar to the `Deck` class, but some `Deck` props like `views`, `parent`/`canvas`/`device`, `viewState`/`initialViewState`, and `controller` are either managed internally or disabled because `MapLibre GL JS` handles the core map interactions and camera state when `MapboxOverlay` is used.[3]\n\nWhen utilizing `MapboxOverlay`, you primarily configure the `deck.gl` specific behavior through the options passed to `MapboxOverlay` (e.g., `layers`, `interleaved`). `MapLibre GL JS` options are set during the initial `maplibregl.Map` instantiation.[1]\n\n`deck.gl` itself is a GPU-powered framework for data visualization and can function standalone without a base map, but it integrates well with various mapping libraries including `MapLibre GL JS`.[5][8]\n\nSources:\n[1] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHcvoN_LONRWSr0XT1kXABWoG_tWJ76pLIHdZK-m668BBRHDI13XD-ktXPFRbbAkkw1gQvFGZH63FPsWIuLAPAK6oxVKTyE0AX5j-dTWjVAhZdtgco32h-U6yuvouZSAro6VhGbYOMRiZlc6b-FdbYLDq7rPW5BU20cdzweaA==)\n[2] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG1OoetQ7R3FyGghmBBWLLUHuzOiKPGlnv_x4uoJF-yqOqQJeIgg5BI_yBjcHsWY50VfFf64ZFs9dhg5EEcUxT-teSdumvHkPfcQxfAHRGU4fk9aXAEeZAdqsNKjwk0PlcEas1z-Hzz04fjm1Sy)\n[3] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGh9VbWFPBXkmYTdWSHYuXHuI83GcpnTwFYiNKzvY0eImu4sw6USjlTOwYrBeJgEJWDnUuoGIk5wEFxtK0REzF6qA3bgK9lN8RTSZqxNOfsJDh9Hw8VpW-gQHHuIGu_3hX3BZ6KhIUy2fAkNmmJeeus0GbS)\n[4] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH3L4HycrkmbvH1mXl_ji60NY83SqII-pUUoeDyKZfzBnAZHEKOIKOMWRCU981Wr9OIKvnEjGhOmzld2ySsb7NKUpXVfVVXw3I5pvcmAGeDwOb0QoxtSIraPlC_giWll9fgK1WWwxQ4CcBJ_qg=)\n[5] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGGPJkXt6oUWufX_8nPA521vIAs5dFSVZoi6EB3RQXG8B2zI6wVbvoiT_rKTWVXjFwb6tGSy04TcrnGSxFbZ2laFFjTKb4Ly5sUDwXSXdZMegM5cb5p6FOjym918JFIFEHSwa9W_Y04gP7U_S8=)\n[6] [clockworkmicro.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGt7JstVUIU_PJbvmYcFVs33S-Ac5uluMGEupoWqX_QbgwxLP7oXWeQM7HzLD4HewgRoNHqFGpNaLhx4t-_SifmfONL_brNjee5u4ajaMUaBZ0eIa3KOvaNSqNiC4hkYbmrFrUtObPP8v9Df_WhDcYAdtDmfOyoqJUOTKA3-AWPHVu2uj1oEA==)\n[7] [maplibre.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGzdw3WumP5wscSaMdFv5kiMkqZVyWy4DD2YWZDfQvnTrtwSX8UbkQAi9Q5qmu-TVXBY4SUkZoonA4ur4FjuUZOShGZ0I0qix7HsoNjotBWthjC9rfupvks0fydPxm3pPNu_ioITLpjYNh-F47Qu-ZtK-oBWuYeZqILokBTUnvnbJs=)\n[8] [deck.gl](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHxxmIXV7puvEzJ1LFivo9REPJW6wsmQfsalrp2F_Kx_Cj4GwzMrYTsLEiJw1t-HoTcpmHrMoUxtnomCH9oHoHT6vtz3w8esaflCHk=)"
    search_type: SEARCH_WEB_TYPE_WEB
  }
}
